<HEADLINE> Sino-Japanese Scientific Exchanges Center Set Up in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 15 (Xinhua) -- The Sino-Japanese Scientific
Exchanges Center was set up in the Chinese Academy of Sciences
here today.
</P>
<P>
The establishment of the center was an idea of some Chinese
students who had studied in Japan, and it is expected to promote
scientific exchanges between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Sources said that it also marks the 25th anniversary of the
normalization of Sino-Japanese diplomatic relations. 
</P>
