<HEADLINE> Germany Issues Arrest Warrants for Three Iranian Agents </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, May 15 (Xinhua) -- German federal prosecutors announced
today that they have issued arrest warrants for three Iranian
secret service officials in connection with the 1992 killings of
four Kurdish dissidents in Berlin.
</P>
<P>
The announcement, made by the federal prosecutor's office in
Karlsruhe, came five weeks after a Berlin court ruled that Iranian
leaders ordered the killings in Berlin in September 1992.
</P>
<P>
The court ruling has soured the diplomatic relations between
Bonn and Teheran, and prompted Germany and other European Union
countries to temporarily recall their ambassadors to Iran.
</P>
<P>
The prosecutor's office said the three Iranian secret service
officials were charged with murder and attempted murder in
connection with the Berlin attack.
</P>
<P>
An arrest warrant issued last year against Iranian intelligence
minister Ali Fallahiyan suspected of ordering the attack would
remain in force, the office said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
