<HEADLINE> UN Chief Recommends Mandate Renewal of Macedonia Force </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, May 15 (Xinhua) -- U.N. Secretary-General Kofi
Annan recommended on Thursday that the mandate of the U.N.
Preventive Deployment Force (UNPREDEP) in Macedonia be renewed for
an additional six months until 30 November 1997.
</P>
<P>
In his report to the Security Council, Annan stated that it
would be imprudent to recommend that the UNPREDEP mission be
terminated.
</P>
<P>
"As pointed out in my letter of 3 April 1997 to the President
of the Security Council, recent developments in Albania have
demonstrated that stability in the Balkan region remains extremely
fragile," he said. The letter led to a suspension of drawdown of
military component of UNPREDEP by the Security Council.
</P>
<P>
Annan said in light of request of Macedonia for a continued
UNPREDEP presence, the continuation of the conditions that led to
the suspension of the drawdown of the military component, he is of
the view that it would be imprudent to recommend that the UNPREDEP
mission be terminated.  
</P>
</TEXT>
