<BODY>
<HEADLINE> People's Daily Hails Li Peng's African Visit a Success </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 15 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Li Peng's latest
visit to seven African countries has deepened mutual understanding
and promoted traditional friendship, a commentary carried in
Friday's People's Daily said.
</P>
<P>
Li's African tour, highly praised and well received by African
people, is a major diplomatic success coming after Chinese
President Jiang Zemin's historic visit to the continent last year,
the commentary said.
</P>
<P>
During his visit between May 3 and 14, Li met and talked with
leaders of the seven African nations -- Zambia, Mozambique, Gabon,
Cameroun, Nigeria, Tanzania and Seychelles -- on a wide range of
topics and signed more than 20 cooperation agreements.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese premier and the African leaders, by exchanging
ideas, have reached common ground for the further development of
traditional Sino-African friendship and cooperation under new
international conditions.
</P>
<P>
The commentary said, "Africa is a developing continent. It has
more than 50 countries, accounting for nearly a third of the
members of the United Nations and half of the members of the
Non-Aligned Movement".
</P>
<P>
"Therefore, Africa is an important element in safeguarding world
peace and regional stability. It is a vital new force in
changing the unfair and unreasonable old international political
and economic order, and an important influence in pushing the
world towards multi-polarization", said the commentary.
</P>
<P>
"We are happy to see that many African countries are achieving
political stability, seeking social systems and development roads
suited to local conditions, and have made progress in regional
cooperation," it said.
</P>
<P>
Over the past few years, the Organization of African Unity and
other regional organizations have played a more active role in
promoting unity, safeguarding regional peace and promoting
economic development and social progress. Africa is a continent
full of promise.
</P>
<P>
With its vast lands and rich resources, Africa has good natural
conditions and great potential to develop its economy. The
comparatively backward economic development in Africa today is the
aftermath of hundreds years of colonial rule and plunder, and the
consequence of the prevailing unreasonable international economic
order.
</P>
<P>
To help African countries in their economic development, the
commentary said, China has, in the decades since their
independence, provided them with the aid which was within its
power to give. The sincere aid from China, although small in
amount, has been warmly received in Africa, especially in view of
its extension without political strings attached.
</P>
<P>
China and African countries, which are all developing nations,
have been the victims of unequal trade and discriminatory economic
policies. With common historical traits, common development
objectives and common interests, cooperation between China and
African countries is based on equality.
</P>
<P>
China and African countries, having their own respective
strengths, can promote economic cooperation by giving full play to
their economic complementarity. African countries welcome Chinese
enterprises to start joint ventures there.
</P>
<P>
China believes there is great potential for economic
cooperation based on equality, mutual respect and mutual
benefit. China's reforms to its aid delivery and economic
cooperation has been understood and supported by most African
countries.
</P>
<P>
In the future, the commentary said, China will emphasize
enterprise-level cooperation while providing assistance to the
African continent to the best of its ability.
</P>
<P>
Strengthening consultation and friendly cooperation between
China, the largest developing country, and Africa, the largest
developing continent, will be of great importance to world peace,
stability and development and will have a far-reaching influence
on creating a better world and taking it into the next century, it
said.
</P>
<P>
Premier Li's visit to Africa has strengthened the long-lasting
friendship and cooperation between China and African countries. We
believe this friendship and cooperation will bear rich fruit, the
commentary said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
