<HEADLINE> Zambia Accused of Expelling Mozambicans </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, May 15 (Xinhua) -- The police authorities in
northwestern Mozambique's Tete Province has accused Zambia of
expelling Mozambicans out of that country.
</P>
<P>
Some Mozambicans living in Zambia were even beaten and
arrested, the Mozambique Information Agency today quoted
unidentified policemen in the province as saying.
</P>
<P>
The policemen said relations between the Zambians and the
Mozambicans in the border areas have not been harmonious since
former President Kenneth Kaunda stepped down from power.
</P>
<P>
Tete Governor Virgilio Ferrao also admitted that there are
some "problems" in the common border areas.
</P>
<P>
However, Ken Nankinza, Military Attache in the Zambian Embassy
here said he did not know anything about the matter. enditem

