<HEADLINE> Zyuganov Calls for More Active Russian Role in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, May 15 (Xinhua) -- Gennady Zyuganov, secretary
general of Russia's Communist Party, who is currently touring
the Middle East, today urged the Russian government to play
a more active role in the region.
</P>
<P>
Zyuganov, who arrived here from Damascus this morning, held
meetings with Lebanese President Elias Hrawi, Deputy House
Speaker Elie Frizli as well as Walid Jumblatt, chairman of
Lebanon's Progressive Socialist Party and minister of the
displaced.
</P>
<P>
The Russian communist leader said that "in a friendly and
cordial atmosphere" he and the Lebanese president exchanged
views on various issues especially the Middle East peace
process.
</P>
<P>
Talking to reporters at the end of the meeting, Zyuganov
urged all parties involved in the peace process to implement all
resolutions adopted by the United Nations and its Security
Council.
</P>
<P>
"We believe that the priority in Russia's foreign policy
should be linked with an increasing activation of its relations
with the Arab states, in the middle east and especially in
supporting resolutions of the Security Council," he said.
</P>
<P>
He said that he held talks in Damascus Wednesday with
Syrian President Hafez al-Assad and other officials on issues in
the region and bilateral relations between the Russian Communist
Party and the Syrian Arab Socialist Baath Party.
</P>
<P>
Zyuganov noted that the position of Yevgeny Primakov, the
Russian foreign minister, was not different from that of the
communist-dominant Russian parliament.
</P>
<P>
He said that the position of the majority was to support
the peaceful ways which should be practised in the region for a
settlement of the Middle East problem, and the commitment to the
legitimate right and resolutions of the United Nations.
</P>
<P>
"For this reason, we call for an activation of Russia's
relations with Syria and Lebanon and a support for the two
countries in Russia's foreign policy," he said, adding that his
visit will contribute to the cooperation with the two Arab
states.
</P>
<P>
At the end of his meeting with Frizli, Zyuganov underlined
that the peace process needs a unification and cooperation of
those powers who have interests in the peace.
</P>
<P>
"Russia should be more active in playing its role in this
region and in supporting all the peaceful moves of Syria and
Lebanon," he reiterated. 
</P>
</TEXT>
