<HEADLINE> EAC Passports to Be Issued in Septmeber </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, May 15 (Xinhua) -- The East African
Co-operation (EAC) passports launched in Arusha, Northern
Tanzania on April 29, will be issued to the public in September,
EAC Executive Secretary Francis Muthaura said today.
</P>
<P>
In a telephone interview with the local Daily News from
Arusha, Francis Muthaura said the travelling documents are being
produced in Britain.
</P>
<P>
"We have ordered 300,000 passports, 100,000 for each member
country of the EAC - Kenya, Uganda and Tanzania. We expect to
receive the first batch in August," said Muthaura.
</P>
<P>
He said the introduction of the EAC passports is aimed at
promoting trade among the east African states and easing
cross-border movements of the East Africans.
</P>
<P>
The regional passport is only valid in East Africa.
</P>
<P>
Kenyan President Daniel Arap Moi, Ugnadan President Yoweri
Museveni and Tanzanian President Benjamin Mkapa launched the
passports on April 29 at the Sheikh Amri Abeid Stadium in Arusha,
urging East Africans to make full use of the documents.
</P>
<P>
On the EAC flag, Muthaura said the Permanent Tripartite
Commission has decided that it be hoisted at the EAC headquarters
in Arusha and at the ministries responsiblle for regional
co-operation in the three countries.
</P>
<P>
The flags will also be hosted at the international airports
and harbours of the member states, immigration posts at border
towns and a few places to be allowed by the commission later.
</P>
</TEXT>
