<HEADLINE> Athens Stock Prices Edge Towards New Record </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, May 15 (Xinhua) -- Stock prices moved closer to an
all-time high on the Athens Stock Exchange today.
</P>
<P>
The general index closed 0.54 percent higher at 1,643.51 points
reflecting gains in the industrial and leasing sectors, which
ended 4.06 and 1.52 percent higher respectively.
</P>
<P>
A drop in the inflation rate and falling interest rates have
reportedly set the scene for the historic rally in prices, as
investors are shifting from bank deposits and bond holdings to
equities after interest rates dropped to single digits for the
first time in years.
</P>
<P>
Banks rose 0.51 percent, insurance ended 0.35 percent up,
investment increased 0.76 percent, construction fell 0.35 percent,
holding dropped 1.49 percent and various eased 0.70 percent. the
parallel market index rose 1.24 percent.
</P>
<P>
Trading was extremely heavy and turnover reached 34.5 billion
drachmas (about 93.15 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
In the main market, advancers led decliners by 128 to 105 with
another 22 issues remaining unchanged. 
</P>
