<HEADLINE> New Anti-Cancer Substance Found </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, May 15 (Xinhua) -- A Cypriot scientist in the United
States has announced he has composed a chemical substance that
destroys malignant cells, which was described as a major leap
forward in battle against cancer.
</P>
<P>
Kyriakos Nicolaou, who has taught and conducted research in
several U.S. universities since 1972, told the Cyprus
Broadcasting Corporation (CyBC) today that the chemical substance
known as Epothilone can destroy malignant cells which proved
resistant to the preparation drug Taxol, also discovered by
Nicolaou.
</P>
<P>
Taxol is considered a revolutionary drug because it has
produced remarkable results against malignant melanoma, breast
cancer and ovarian cancer, CyBC said.
</P>
<P>
Dr. Nicolaou said the importance of his discovery rests on the
fact that this chemical compound acts effectively where other
drugs cannot. But he did not elaborate on the chemical.
</P>
<P>
He added that it will be three years until the perfected drug
reaches the market.
</P>
<P>
Nicolaou, 51, is president of the Scripps Institute in La
Jolla, California, and is a professor at California's San Diego
University.
</P>
<P>
He has also synthesised many other chemical compounds in
the fight against cancer, hyper-cholesterinaemia and other diseases.
</P>
</TEXT>
