<HEADLINE> Retired French General Predicts "Pitched Battle" </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, May 15 (Xinhua) -- Former chief of staff of the French
army, General Jeannou Lacaze, said today that there will surely be
a "pitched battle" for Kinshasa between Zairian government
forces and the rebel forces of Laurent-Desire Kabila.
</P>
<P>
Lacaze, who also served as chief of staff of the presidential
office and personal advisor of President Mobutu Sese Seko, told
Agence France-Presse that the rebel forces are from now on meeting
more serious resistance from government troops backed by former
Angolan rebel soldiers of Jonas Savimbi.
</P>
<P>
