without having any pitched battle. There will surely be a pitched
battle for the possession of Kinshasa. It is possible because, as
the Zairian forces are narrowing (their front), they will gain
strength," he said.
</P>
<P>
Lacaze, who recently toured Zaire for humanitarian purposes and
met with both Mobutu and Kabila, said that although Mobutu is
sick, "he is not a man who will say I go and leave the place to
Kabila."
</P>
<P>
"He will surely try, with the help of the Europeans, the
Westerners, to leave an intermediary (to succeed his power),"
said the general, who is widely regarded as an expert on Zaire.
</P>
