<DOCNO> XIE19970516.0050 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-05-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Poor, Minority American Students Lack Access to Computers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, May 15 (Xinhua) -- Poor and minority American
students have significantly less access to computers in their
classrooms than do more affluent children, a report by the
Educational Testing Service said.
</P>
<P>
Schools nationwide now have one computer roughly for every 10
students, while the ratio of students to computer is 17 to 1 at
schools where minority enrollment exceeds 90 percent, the report
said.
</P>
<P>
The ratio is even higher for more expensive computers with
enhanced graphics and interactive video capabilities. At schools
with a large minority enrollment, the ratio is 30 students for one
computer, at high-poverty schools, the ratio is near 35 to 1,
compared with a ration closer to 20 to 1 at other schools.
</P>
<P>
The report said that about one-third of high school seniors use
computers at least a few times a week to complete some of their
class work. But 37 percent of seniors never use computers, and at
many schools Internet access is still limited to one site.
</P>
<P>
The report also asserted that most teachers lack the education
and training they need to use technology effectively in their
classes. Only 15 percent of teachers have taken at least nine
hours of training in computer education. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970516.0051 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-05-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Two Israelis Fined for Diamond Smuggling </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, May 15 (Xinhua) -- Two Israeli women, arrested
today at Johannesburg International Airport last Saturday for
possession of more than 3000 uncut diamonds, were each fined
200,000 Rand (about 45000 US Dollar) in a regional court here.
</P>
<P>
Dina Buzaglo, 53, and her daughter, Tamar Schwartz, 32, both
from Tel Aviv, pleaded guilty on charges of possession of the
diamonds to the value of 3.5 million Rand (about 778000 US
Dollar).
</P>
<P>
They were alternatively sentenced to two years' imprisonment.
</P>
<P>
The two were arrested minutes before boarding a flight to
Israel. They tried to take the diamonds out of the country in
five condoms hidden in their private parts.
</P>
<P>
In their statement to the Magistrate they claimed they were on
holiday in South Africa and were approached by a person to take
the diamonds to Israel.
</P>
<P>
They decided to take up the offer for financial needs and
picked up the diamonds from a Johannesburg hotel, but could not
give the court any further details on the whereabouts of the
person who approached them. 
</P>
</TEXT>
