<HEADLINE> CD-ROMs to Offer Shanghai Information </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, May 16 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai today published CD-ROMs
to provide comprehensive information concerning the country's
largest city.
</P>
<P>
The compact discs, believed to be the first of their kind in
China, give details of every aspect of Shanghai, such as history,
politics, law, economy and science, by using 30 million Chinese
characters, 3,000 charts, 300 electronic maps and a 25-minute-long
cartoon film.
</P>
<P>
The city sources said that more than 1,200 researchers spent
nearly two years developing the CD-ROM.
</P>
<P>
The publishing of the disc will greatly benefit the opening-up
and economic development of the country's industrial and
commercial center, while promoting the electronic publications
industry, said an official with the municipal government.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for the publisher, the Shanghai Joint Publishing
Book Store, said that it would renew the edition of the disc
annually. 
