<HEADLINE> Shenzhen, HK Authorities Jointly Dredge Boundary River </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, May 16 (Xinhua) -- The authorities in Shenzhen of
Guangdong Province and Hong Kong started to dredge their boundary
river, the Shenzhen River, today in a bid to reduce the flood risk
and improve the environment in both places.
</P>
<P>
The authorities plan to invest 900 million yuan (about 108
million US dollars) in the second phase of the dredging project.
</P>
<P>
A 6.8-km section of the river will be widened and dredged, and
the dykes on both sides will be repaired during the next three and
a half years.
</P>
<P>
The first phase of the project, which began in May 1995, was
completed last month, covering a 3.2-km section of the river.
</P>
