<HEADLINE> Ivanisevic Enters Semi-finals at Italian Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, May 16 (Xinhua) -- Sixth-seeded Goran Ivanisevic of
Croatia stopped Scott Draper of Australia in the quarter-finals at
the Italian Open tennis tournament on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Ivanisevic, the highest-ranked survivor at the tournament, beat
giant-killer Draper 6-4, 6-4. Draper eliminated defending
champion and third-seeded Thomas Muster of Austria earlier in the
week.
</P>
<P>
Ivanisevic, playing his first tournament since breaking a
finger last March, broke Draper once in each set.
</P>
<P>
He broke Draper at 3-2 in the first set and 4-3 in the second
set to win the match in just over one hour.
</P>
<P>
Ivanisevic is just one of three seeds left in the tournament.
The other survivors are seventh seed Marcelo Rios of Chile and
10th-seeded Alex Corretja of Spain. 
</P>
</TEXT>
