<HEADLINE> Chirac Says China Trip Achieves Goals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 16 (Xinhua) -- French President Jacques Chirac
highly praised the comprehensive Sino-French partnership and
expressed satisfaction over the results of his visit to China here
this evening.
</P>
<P>
He told a press conference that the Joint Sino-French
Declaration that he and Chinese President Jiang Zemin signed this
morning is the most important document in bilateral relations
since 1964. He said that the joint declaration provides a solid
foundation for the establishment of a comprehensive partnership
between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
He told the press conference that he is satisfied with the
results of cooperation between French enterprises and the Chinese
side. He noted that great progress has been made in bilateral
cooperation in various fields including civil aviation, energy,
agriculture and grain products.
</P>
<P>
He announced that he has achieved the major goals he set for
his China trip.
</P>
<P>
In response to a question, he pointed out that both France and
China agree that, in a multi-polarized world, all countries should
carry out dialogue on an equal footing.
</P>
<P>
In a lecture at the China's National School of Administration
in northwestern Beijing, Chirac said that France, along with its
partners in the European Union, has initiated a constructive
dialogue with China on the basis of mutual trust. He said that
this is a dialogue between two partners and two great
civilizations that understand and respect each other. 
</P>
</TEXT>
