<HEADLINE> Fuzhou Center to Boost Cross-Straits Cultural Exchanges </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, May 16 (Xinhua) -- A center for the promotion of
cultural exchanges between Fujian Province and Taiwan was set up
today in this capital city of east China's Fujian Province.
</P>
<P>
Fujian and Taiwan are separated only by the Taiwan Straits, and
the people in both places share the same dialect and culture.
</P>
<P>
The Fujian-Taiwan Cultural Center, set up by the Fujian
provincial government, is planning to hold a series of exhibitions
and other cultural activities in Taiwan this year.
</P>
<P>
Sources said that since 1990 some 409 Fujian artists have visited
Taiwan, and 757 Taiwan artists have visited Fujian.  
</P>
</TEXT>
