<HEADLINE> Italian Soccer Stars to Visit Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, May 16 (Xinhua) -- Italian soccer giants Inter Milan
will visit Hong Kong next month to play against local senior side
of Sing Tao, the organizers confirmed here Friday.
</P>
<P>
The announcement quells weeks of speculation regarding the
nature of the teams competing at the Hong Kong Stadium on June 18,
which will be one of the major sporting events before Hong Kong's
return to the motherland at midnight on June 30 this year.
</P>
<P>
In a dramatic move for sports fans, the 13-time Italian league
champions readily accepted the opportunity to bring their
sensational line-up to Asia.
</P>
<P>
And organizers were delighted that Hong Kong could play host to
the Milan side, which is one of the world soccer's most
celebrated and successful club sides.
</P>
<P>
Among the big names on the team's second appearance in Hong
Kong will be such bountifully skilled midfielders as Frenchman
Youri Djorkaeff, experienced Dutchman Aron Winter and in-form
England star Paul Ince, Chilean international forward Ivan
Zamorano and Argentina's star defender Javier Zanetti.
</P>
<P>
Sing Tao has been very successful this season, already with
three major local titles to their credit -- Viceroy Cup, Regional
Council Cup and F.A. President Cup.
</P>
<P>
"With our triumph over South China days ago, I can say we have
now grasped half of the F.A. Cup trophy," said Ng Chung, chairman
of Sing Tao Sports Club Ltd. at today's press conference.
</P>
</TEXT>
