<HEADLINE> Panel Formed in Nepal to Observe Local Polls </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, May 16 (Xinhua) -- A special committee has been set
up in Nepal to observe the imminent local elections across the
country, sources here said today.
</P>
<P>
The 38-member Election Observation Committee, mainly comprising
legal experts, intellectuals, human rights activists, social
workers and journalists, will send teams to watch election
proceedings in 19 of the country's 75 districts.
</P>
<P>
The committee later will also make its report public after
scrutinizing and checking the validity of media reports published
during the election period on election-related activities,
committee members said.
</P>
<P>
Some West Nepali districts, where an underground armed leftist
movement has called for boycotting the elections and unleashed
insurgency to block them, were on the top of the committee's list
for observation, they said.
</P>
<P>
Voters in West Nepal are to elect leaderships of local bodies
at various levels including the village and municipality on
Saturday while the polls in Central and East Nepal will be held on
May 26. 
</P>
</TEXT>
