<HEADLINE> China Trains More Army Logistics Officers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 16 (Xinhua) -- China has trained at least 25,000
army logistics officers, sources revealed here today at a meeting
to mark the 45th anniversary of the Academy of Logistics Command
of the Chinese People's Liberation Army.
</P>
<P>
Chinese President and Chairman of the Central Military
Commission Jiang Zemin, as well as Vice-Chairman of the Commission
Liu Huaqing, wrote words of congratulations for the celebration.
</P>
