train from Taiyuan, the capital of north China's Shanxi Province,
to Beijing will be equipped with mobile phones for passengers to
use.
</P>
<P>
The service will be provided by the Beijing Wireless
Telecommunications Administration.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Jiaji, director of the administration, said that his
administration will install mobile phones on all the trains
running on the Beijing-Kowloon Railway before July 1 to
celebrate Hong Kong's return to China.
</P>
<P>
The administration has already provided mobile phones aboard
the two express tourism trains from Beijing to Qinhuangdao, a
summer resort in north China's Hebei Province. 
