<HEADLINE> Switzerland Blocks Sale of Mobutu's Villa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, May 16 (Xinhua) -- The Swiss government today announced
it was blocking the sale of Zairean President Mobutu Sese Seko's
luxury villa near Geneva, reports said here.
</P>
<P>
The move comes following a request from a prosecutor in Zaire's
second largest city Lubumbashi, now held by rebel forces, to
freeze the embattled president's assets in Switzerland, including
his property and bank accounts.
</P>
<P>
Swiss media have estimated the villa's worth at between 2.5
million and 5 million U.S. dollars and Mobutu's total assets in the
country at about 4 billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
Mobutu, whose government troops have been fighting rebel forces
led by Laurent Kabila for several months, reportedly fled the
Zairean caital of Kinshasa earlier today for Morocco after rebels
closed in on the city. 
</P>
</TEXT>
