<HEADLINE> Bangladesh to Get ADB Financial Assistance </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, May 16 (Xinhua) -- Bangladesh will receive over 400
million U.S. dollars in assistance from the Asian Development Bank
(ADB) this year, 170 million dollars more than last year, Finance
Minister Shah Kibria said here today.
</P>
<P>
Talking to reporters at the airport on his return from a
meeting of the ADB Board of Governors held in Japan, the minister
said Japan would also provide about 130 million dollars in loans
to Bangladesh this year.
</P>
<P>
Kibria termed the development of relations with the ADB and
Japan during his visit as significant in the context of future
economic development through international cooperation.
</P>
<P>
"I am very pleased to say that the shadow which was casting
over relations between Bangladesh and the two major bilateral
donors is being removed successfully," he said.
</P>
<P>
The minister said his visit was for making preparations for
Prime Minister Sheikh Hasina's visit to Japan in July. "I have
returned with a firm belief that a new horizon of cooperation will
open up between Tokyo and Dhaka during the forthcoming visit."
</P>
