<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Joins World Accountants Federation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 16 (Xinhua) -- China was unanimously voted into
the International Federation of Accountants last Thursday, an
important sign that Chinese accountants are merging with the world
market.
</P>
<P>
This is another achievement made by the Chinese Institute of
Certified Public Accountants (CICPA) after it became a council
member of the Confederation of Asian-Pacific Accountants at the
end of April this year.
</P>
<P>
All these successes indicate that Chinese accountants are
getting closer to internationally accepted accounting norms,
officials with the CICPA said.
</P>
<P>
China resumed its certified public accountants (CPA) system in
the early 1980s, and the accountancy profession has become the
fastest growing, the most attractive and the most promising new
industry in the service sector as the nation is shifting to a
socialist market economy, said the CICPA officials.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that there are a total of 124,000 CPAs in
China, with 58,000 of them working with agencies. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
