<DOCNO> XIE19970516.0088 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-05-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Noted Chinese Organic Chemist Dies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, May 16 (Xinhua) -- Wang You, China's leading organic
chemist, died here on May 6, at the age of 87.
</P>
<P>
A pioneer in the field of organic chemistry, Wang was
an academician of the Chinese Academy of Sciences (CAS) and the
honorary director of the Shanghai Institute of Organic Chemistry
under the CAS.
</P>
<P>
Because of Wang's contributions, China took the lead in the
world in research into "total synthesis of crystaline bovine
insulin" and "total synthesis of yeast alanine transfer
ribonucleic acid". He also led studies on the chemistry of
trichosanthin.
</P>
<P>
Wang was an honorary member of the French Academy of Sciences
and the Bavarian Academy of Sciences of Germany. He was also an
honorary member of the American Society of Biochemistry and
Molecular Biology.
</P>
<P>
In the political sphere Wang was a member of the Standing
Committee of the Second National Committee of the Chinese People's
Political Consultative Congress and a deputy to the second,
third, fifth and sixth National People's Congresses. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970516.0089 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-05-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> PLA Needs More Modernized Training, Education </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, May 16 (Xinhua) -- A Chinese military leader has
urged the People's liberation Army (PLA), China's armed forces, to
speed up the modernization of its training and education to turn
out better-qualified officers.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Wannian, vice-chairman of the Central Military
Commission, made the remark during a two-day inspection of the PLA
Officers Academy May 15 and 16.
</P>
<P>
He urged the whole armed forces and military training
institutes to further research into maneuvers, especially the use
of advanced simulation systems before the year 2000.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, both officers and men must master high technology,
said Zhang, adding that this is a strategic task.
</P>
<P>
He noted that it is important for military academies to make
more efforts to improve the quality of teaching staff and deepen
reforms of the teaching system to train officers who can meet the
challenges stemming from the military development in the world.
</P>
<P>
He called on scientists to step up research into military
theories and the improvement of weapons and equipment. 
</P>
</TEXT>
