<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Guangdong, HK Police Carry out Anti-Smuggling Maneuvers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, May 16 (Xinhua) -- Police in south China's Guangdong
Province joined their Hong Kong colleagues today in a maneuver
targeted at halting smuggling across the Dapeng Bay.
</P>
<P>
It was the first time that police from Guangdong and Hong Kong
had joined hands in training to intercept smugglers in the waters
near Hong Kong, 46 days before the territory returns to China.
</P>
<P>
About 850 police officers in 22 patrol boats and 35 motor boats
of the Guangdong Border Police Brigade joined the exercise,
together with 80 Hong Kong policemen in ten motor boats.
</P>
<P>
In the course of the maneuvers, the Guangdong policemen
intercepted 20 supposed smuggling boats bound for Hong Kong, some
of which broke through the blockade but were finally arrested by
Hong Kong police.
</P>
<P>
The maneuvers were intended to improve cooperation between the
Guangdong and Hong Kong police forces in the fight against
smugglers, according to Lin Jieyuan, commander of the GBPB.
</P>
</TEXT>
