<HEADLINE> Cheng Leads Second Round at China Open Golf </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 16 (Xinhua) -- Cheng Jun of China led after the
second round in the China Open golf tournament at Beijing
International Golf Club on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The 28-year-old Cheng carded a best of the day two-under-par
70 for a half-way total of two-under-par 142 and a one stroke
lead over first-round leader Hsieh Yu-shu of Chinese Taipei.
</P>
<P>
Cheng birdied his first two holes of the day and that gave him
a lot of confidence.
</P>
<P>
Only four players in the field of 144 broke par. American
Mike Cunning carded a one-under-par 71 to finish the day in third
place.
</P>
<P>
Cheng has lived in the shadow of compatriot Zhang Lianwei for
the past couple of years. He turned professional in 1994 but
failed to fulfill his potential.
</P>
<P>
India's Vivek Bandhari, David Bransdon and Rob Stephens of
Australia, Eric Meeks of the United States and Steven Armstrong
of Scotland are in a tie for fourth place on two over par for the
tournament. 
</P>
