<HEADLINE> Chinese Premier Meets Japanese Guests </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 16 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Li Peng met here
today with Nishigaki Akira, president of the Overseas Economic
Cooperation Fund (OECF) of Japan.
</P>
<P>
Li said that the OECF, as the executive body for Japanese
government loans, has maintained sound cooperative ties with
the Chinese Ministry of Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation
(MOFTEC) and other relevant departments of China.
</P>
<P>
He said that with the concerted efforts of China and Japan the
first three batches of Japanese government loans to China have
been used successively and have played a major role in
China's economic development.
</P>
<P>
Li spoke highly of the OECF's efforts to implement the loan
projects. He said that he hoped that Akira would make on-the-spot
investigations of the projects for which loans were used in order
to make a proper assessment of the Chinese side's implementation
of the loans.
</P>
<P>
Akira said that he had visited China in 1990 and had been
deeply impressed.
</P>
<P>
He said that the successful use of Japanese government loans
in China resulted from the Chinese government's support and
China's reform and opening-up policy. The effective use of the loans
by the Chinese government has won praise and support from
the Japanese people for the cooperation.
</P>
<P>
He said that the OECF and he himself will continue their
efforts to make the loaning a success.
</P>
<P>
Akira is here at the invitation of MOFTEC. 
