<HEADLINE> Li Peng Meets Malaysian Foreign Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 16 (Xinhua) -- China values its relations with its
neighboring countries, its friendly contacts with the Association
of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN) and its close cooperation with
Malaysia, Chinese Premier Li Peng said here today.
</P>
<P>
China adopts an independent foreign policy of peace, Li added.
</P>
<P>
The premier made the remarks in a meeting here this afternoon
with visiting Malaysian Foreign Minister Datuk Abdullah Bin Haji
Badawi.
</P>
<P>
Li noted that in recent years Sino-Malaysian relations, through
joint efforts, have achieved positive progress in various fields,
and leaders of the two countries have frequently exchanged visits,
indicating a good situation for bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
China appreciates Malaysia's efforts to promote ASEAN-China
relations, and hopes to join hands with Malaysia to set up
good-neighborly relations of mutual trust and cooperation oriented
to the coming 21st century, Li said.
</P>
<P>
He thanked Malaysia for its support for China on international
and regional issues, including the human rights issue.
</P>
<P>
Badawi said Malaysia attaches importance to its friendly ties
with China and hopes to further expand and deepen bilateral
cooperation in various sectors.
</P>
<P>
Malaysia appreciates the constructive policy China adopts
toward the ASEAN, with the hope of making its due contribution to
the enhancement of friendly cooperative relations between ASEAN
and China, he said.
</P>
<P>
Praising China's independent foreign policy of peace, Badawi
noted that both sides had reached common understanding on a wide
range of international and regional issues.
</P>
<P>
He said that he hoped that the existing relations of extensive
cooperation would continue.
</P>
<P>
Badawi passed on to Li regards from Malaysian Prime Minister
Mahathir Mohamad and repeated Mahathir's invitation for Li to
visit Malaysia.
</P>
<P>
Li expressed his thanks and accepted the invitation with
pleasure. He also asked Badawi to convey his best wishes to
Mahathir. 
