<DOCNO> XIE19970516.0101 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-05-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Gun Trader Sentenced to 14 Years in Prison (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DALIAN, May 16 (Xinhua) -- A man convicted of exporting 2,000
AK-47 rifles to the US was today sentenced to 14 years in prison
in this port city in northeast China's Liaoning Province.
</P>
<P>
In an open trial today the Dalian City Intermediate People's
Court handed down the sentence to Qi Feng, former manager of the
Duoweidi Science and Technology Co. Ltd. in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Three other people, Lu Yilun, Qin Qixiu and Guo
Chengkun, were sentenced at the same trial to three to four years
imprisonment for dereliction of duty.
</P>
<P>
The court found that in July 1995 Qi Feng and Gu Hanqun, an
American businessman, jointly schemed to purchase disassembled
rifles in China for re-sale in the US.
</P>
<P>
In the same month Qi Feng contacted Qin Qixiu, an employee of
the China North Industries Dalian Corporation, and expressed the
intention of seeking customs clearance for exporting gun parts to the
US in the name of Qin's company.
</P>
<P>
Qin agreed and reported to Lu Yilun, assistant to the general
manager of the China North Industries Dalian Corporation. Lu
immediately approved the deal without asking the higher
authorities for instructions, and asked another company employee,
Guo Chengkun, to help Qin in the business.
</P>
<P>
In January 1996 Gu Hanqun and Qi Feng talked with Qin Qixiu and
Guo Chengkun, and reached an agreement to sell 2,000 disassembled
AK-47 rifles in the US after Gu had agreed to provide a US
import license.
</P>
<P>
On January 25, Qi Feng received from Gu Hanqun an import
license issued by the Alcohol, Tobacco and Firearms Bureau of the
US Treasury Department. Numbered 94-06831, the license approved
the import of 2,000 sets of AK-47 rifle parts from China.
</P>
<P>
Then Qi used counterfeit documents to order 2,000 sets of
parts of the AK-47 rifles at an ordnance repair workshop,
which, according to the contract, repaired 2,000 sets of
discarded rifle parts, and sold them to Qi.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
