<DOCNO> XIE19970516.0103 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-05-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Gun Trader Sentenced to 14 Years in Prison (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Following discussions between Qi Feng and Qin Qixiu, Guo
Chengkun helped Qi to clear customs in the name of the China North
Industries Dalian Corporation. The rifle parts arrived in the US
on February 15, 1996.
</P>
<P>
Qi Feng, who was arrested on December 18, 1996, earned 340,000
RMB yuan in profit and a certain amount of US dollars from the deal.
</P>
<P>
The court noted that all the above-mentioned facts had been
proved by spoken and written testimonies and material evidence, as
well as by the confessions of the four defendants during the trial.
</P>
<P>
It held that Qi Feng, who had turned a blind eye to Chinese law
and engaged in the illicit purchase and export of guns, had
seriously endangered public security and was guilty of trading
guns illegally.
</P>
<P>
It said that the sentence was handed down in accordance with the
stipulations of Article 112 of the Criminal Law of the People's
Republic of China.
</P>
<P>
It also concluded that Qin Qixiu, Guo Chengkun and Lu Yilun
were guilty of dereliction of duty, for they had failed to perform
their duties as employees of state-owned enterprises, and had
violated the explicit stipulations of their company by helping Qi
to clear customs and export the gun parts.
</P>
<P>
The case was prosecuted by the Dalian City People's
Procuratorate, and the Dalian City Intermediate People's Court
formed a collegiate bench in accordance with the law after
accepting the case.
</P>
<P>
The trial was attended by the defenders of the four accused, as
well as by people from all walks of life and a number of
journalists. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
