<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 16 (Xinhua) -- Vice-Premier Zhu Rongji met in
Beijing today with some outstanding workers from supply and
marketing cooperatives and congratulated them on behalf of Premier
Li Peng and the State Council.
</P>
<P>
The supply and marketing cooperatives, which were set up in the
1950s, are collectively-owned trade agencies for Chinese
farmers. Nearly 200 million households in rural areas are a part
of this system.
</P>
<P>
Li Peng said yesterday that the supply and marketing
cooperatives should be run better so that they could help develop
the rural economy and help farmers achieve prosperity. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
