<HEADLINE> India to Spend More on Education </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, May 16 (Xinhua) -- The Indian government plans to
earmark 6 percent of the country's gross domestic product (GDP)
for education by the year 2000 compared to 3.5 percent at present,
the Press Trust of India reported today.
</P>
<P>
