<HEADLINE> Chinese Foreign Trade Minister Meets Japanese Visitors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 16 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Minister of Foreign Trade
and Economic Cooperation (MOFTEC) Wu Yi met here today with
Nishigaki Akira, president of the Overseas Economic Cooperation
Fund (OECF) of Japan.
</P>
<P>
Wu expressed her thanks for the fruitful cooperation between
the Chinese side and OECF, the executive organ for Japanese
governmental loans.
</P>
<P>
She said that OECF and MOFTEC have established solid ties. She
also said that she hoped that the two sides would maintain and
develop such ties, especially in the implementation of the
Japanese governmental loans to China for this year and the last
two years of the fourth batch from 1996 to 2000.
</P>
<P>
Akira said that the OECF will continue to support China's
reform and opening-up drive.
</P>
<P>
It was learned that China has used three batches of Japanese
governmental loans worth a total of 1,600 billion yen for 60
projects from 1979 to 1995. In the first three years of the fourth
batch the two countries have agreed to use 580 billion yen for 40
projects in China. 
</P>
