<DOCNO> XIE19970516.0114 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-05-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Takes Three Golds on Final Day of Weightlifting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PUSAN, May 16 (Xinhua) -- Chinese lifter continued their dominating
power on the final day of the weightlifting tournament at the second
East Asian Games, collecting three from four categories here on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
After Song Zhaomei wo the women's 83kg division with a new world
record in the jerk, Shan Yulong and Cui Wenhua followed to win the
women's over 83-kg and men's 108-kg respectively.
</P>
<P>
The only other gold medal on weightlifting arena of the day went to
Kim Tae Hyun of South Korea in the men's over 108-kg division.
</P>
<P>
Song Zhaomei, who had 107.5 kilograms in the snatch, asked 135.5
kilograms in her third attempt in the clean and jerk, beating the
previous world mark by 0.5 kilograms.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese girl took the crown with a total of 242.5 kilograms.
Chen Shu Chih, from Chinese Taipei, was second at 222.5 kilograms,
with 100 from the snatch and 122.5 from jerk.
</P>
<P>
Kim Soo Hee of South Korea finished third at 207.5.
</P>
<P>
In the women's over 83-kg division, Shan Yulong, who had 105kgs in
the snatch and 142.5 in the jerk, won the fifth title in women's
lifting for China with a total of 247.5kgs.
</P>
<P>
Chen Hsiao Lien, of Chinese Taipei, was second with 242.5kgs. Chen
Hsiao Lien had 105kgs in the snatch and 137.5kgs in the jerk.
</P>
<P>
Arai Miyuki of Japan, who snatched 82.5 and jerked 120kgs, finished
third with a combined total of 202.5kgs.
</P>
<P>
Cui Wenhua, first ever Chinese who won the category in the world
championships in 1995, snatched 192.5kgs and jerked 215kgs for a
winning total of 407.5kgs.
</P>
<P>
Chung Dae Jin, of South Korea, had the silver medal at 395kgs, with
170 from the snatch and 225 in the jerk.
</P>
<P>
Serguei Kopytov of Kazakhstan finished third at 392.5kgs from two
lifts.
</P>
<P>
Kim Tae Hyun won the second gold medal for the host country in
weightlifting when he took the men's over 108kg division in 445kgs.
</P>
<P>
The Korean hercules lifted 195kgs in the snatch and 250kgs in the
jerk.
</P>
<P>
Wei Tiehan, veteran from China, was managed to take the silver
medal at 380 kilograms with 180 from the snatch and 200 in the jerk.
</P>
<P>
Japanese lifter Aoki Nobuaki finished third at 352.5kgs.
</P>
<P>
After five day conmpetitions, Chinese lifters collected 12 gold
medals, with seven from men's division and five in women's section.
</P>
<P>
Women lifters helped Chinese Taipei to finish second in the gold
medal rankings with a collection of four titles.
</P>
<P>
Other three divisions in the men's competition were taken by South
Korea and Kazakhstan, who had two and one respectively.
</P>
<P>
Chinese lifters also set five world records at the games, with four
in women's divisions.
</P>
<P>
Qian Guangjian, secretary-general of the Chinese Weightlifting
Association said:"China is still leading the sport in Asia, especially
in lighter divisions."
</P>
<P>
"But in the heavier categories, we are facing great challenges from
South Koreans and Kazakhstanians," he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970516.0115 </DOCNO>
