<HEADLINE> Mongolian, Kazakhstan Wrestlers Dominate East Asian Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PUSAN, May 16 (Xinhua) -- Mongolia and Kazakhstan took three gold
medals each from eight freestyle wrestling finals at the second East
Asian Games here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Oyunbileg Durevbaatar floored Jung Jin-hyuk of South Korea to win
the 58-kg freestyle title, starting Monglolia's gold-hunting spree
at the current games.
</P>
<P>
Bayanmunkh Gantogtokh added Mongolia the second by outwitting
another South Korean entry of Kim Tae-ho in the 97-kg category while
Dolgorsuren Sumiyabazar beat Japanese Hiroyuki Obata in the finals of
the 125-kg class.
</P>
<P>
Kazakhstan also harvest three gold medals through Maoulen Mamyrov,
Magomed Kurugliyev and Elmadi Zhabrailov.
</P>
<P>
Maoulen outscored Chikara Tanabe of Japan 3-1 in the 54-kg class,
Magomed defeated Moon Eui-jae of South Korea in the 76-kg category
while Elmadi beat Ganhuyag Ganzorig of Mongolia in the 85-kg finals.
</P>
<P>
The host awarded the home fans with two gold medals as Nor
Won-chang outwitted Yu Tao of China in the 63-kg and Hwang Sang-ho
beat down Ryusaburo Katsu in the 69-kg class. 
</P>
</TEXT>
