<HEADLINE> Graf Beaten at German Open Women's Tennis Tourney </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BERLIN, May 16 (Xinhua) -- Steffi Graf suffered a humiliating
defeat on Friday as she lost to Amanda Coetzer of South Africa
6-0, 6-1 at the German Open.
</P>
<P>
It was one of the worst defeats for Graf, the former world
number one player who dominated women's tennis for a decade.
</P>
<P>
Returning from a three-month layoff due to a knee injury, Graf
just managed to win a game in the quarter-final match against the
10th-seeded Coetzer.
</P>
<P>
Graf lost her world number one ranking to Martina Hingis in her
absence. She made a lot of errors in the match which last for
less than one hour. 
</P>
