<HEADLINE> Farmers Greet HK's Return to China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, May 16 (Xinhua) -- An exhibition highlighting Hong
Kong's fishery and agriculture opened here today, as the start of
a series of activities to mark Hong Kong's return to China.
</P>
<P>
Dozens of agricultural groups in the New Territories displayed
a variety of aquatic and farm produce, including vegetables, hens,
pigs, flowers and fish.
</P>
<P>
Agronomists from China's Shenzhen and Guangzhou cities shared
their latest research achievements with their Hong Kong
counterparts, including the cultivation of pollution-free
vegetables and health promotional foods.
</P>
<P>
The three-day exhibition was organized by Hong Kong
Agricultural Committee for the Celebration of Hong Kong's Return
to China, a non-governmental organization.  
</P>
</TEXT>
