<HEADLINE> HK Revised Ordinance Proposals Welcomed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, May 16 (Xinhua) -- The revised package of amendments
to the Public Order Ordinance and the Societies Ordinance
published on Thursday by the Chief Executive's Office of the Hong
Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR) has been warmly welcomed
by many local political parties, social groups and individuals.
</P>
<P>
Today's local press widely covered public responses to the
revised package.
</P>
<P>
The Democratic Alliance for the Betterment of Hong Kong held
that the revised package shows that the Chief Executive is able to
hear and respect public opinions submitted during the three-week
consultation period.
</P>
<P>
The alliance also expressed support for the Chief Executive to
make further revisions on the bills so that they can better suit
the interests of Hong Kong people and the practical social
conditions.
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong Progressive Alliance expressed satisfaction and
support for the revised bills, saying that the bills made clear
some confusing concepts in the consultation document and freed the
 public from doubts about the amendments to the bills.
</P>
<P>
It held that the revised package indicates that the Chief
Executive's Office respects public opinions with an open attitude
and is sincere in protecting individual rights and freedom.
</P>
<P>
The Liberal Democratic Federation fully accepted the revised
package, stressing that the revised package has absorbed public
opinion through sincere consultation. It believes that the bills
will be generally accepted by the public.
</P>
<P>
Liberal Party vice-chairman Ronald Arculli said the party
supported the whole package.
</P>
<P>
The revised package will be put before members of the
Provisional Legislative Council this weekend.  
</P>
