<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 169 New Firms Established in Macao in First Quarter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, May 16 (Xinhua) -- Macao saw the founding of 169 new
firms in the first quarter of the year, with their total
registered capital down dramatically.
</P>
<P>
Latest figures released by the Macao Census and Statistics
Department show that the capital of these firms add up only to
25.8 million patacas (about 3.27 million U.S. dollars), down 60.1
percent from the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
Most of the newly-established firms are wholesale and retailing
companies, restaurants and hotels, which account for 44.4 percent.
The rest are construction and public engineering firms and service
sectors.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the figures show that 76 percent of the owners of
the new firms are of local residents.
</P>
<P>
The registered capital of about 84 percent of the new firms is
below 100,000 patacas (about 12,660 U.S. dollars) each.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, eight firms, mostly engaged in construction and
public engineering, were disbanded in the first three months.
Their registered capital reached 5.44 million patacas (about
688,600 U.S. dollars).  
</P>
</TEXT>
