<HEADLINE> 7 Pilgrims Killed in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, May 16 (Xinhua) -- Seven pilgrims, including two
girls, were killed and nine injured in a road mishap in India's
Karnataka state early today, Press Trust of India said.
</P>
<P>
According to local police, the deceased were traveling on top
of the cabin of a truck, which was carrying about 70 passengers,
and died after being badly hit by the arch of an old overbridge.
</P>
<P>
The vehicle was proceeding towards a local pilgrim town when
the tragedy took place.
</P>
<P>
Four person died on the spot and the rest succumbed to their
injuries in hospital.  
