<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Share Prices Continue to Decline on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, May 16 (Xinhua) -- Share prices closed mixed on the
Singapore market as the benchmark Straits Times Industrials Index
continued to decline, falling another 9.24 points to close at
2060.5 today.
</P>
<P>
Total market volume shrank to 129.43 million units, valued at
349.84 million Singapore dollars (about 244.64 million U.S.
dollars). Advances overtook declines by 189 to 125, while 310
other counters remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
MBf Capital was the most actively traded stock as it registered
a turnover of 11.23 million units. It was followed by MBF Holdings
which had 6.94 million shares traded. Poh Lian was next with 5.89
million of its shares changed hands.
</P>
<P>
Local sound cards maker Creative 50 led the gainers of the day
as it rose 80 cents to finish at 26.9 Singapore dollars. NBT
gained 70 cents to end at 11.7 Singapore dollars, while
Diversified Resources closed 40 cents higher at 3.4 Singapore
dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, YTL Corporation was the biggest loser as it
declined 2.85 Singapore dollars to end at 5.55 dollars. Samanda
Holdings fell 2.4 dollars to close at eight Singapore dollars,
while City Developments finished 60 cents lower at 12.7 Singapore
dollars.  
</P>
</TEXT>
