<HEADLINE> PLC to Meet in Shenzhen for Five Bills </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, May 16 (Xinhua) -- The Provisional Legislative
Council (PLC) of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region
(HKSAR) will hold a plenary meeting in Shenzhen Saturday.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, the Secretary for Policy Co-ordination of
the Chief Executive's Office will submit five bills to the
PLC: "Urban Council (Amendment) Bill 1997", "Regional Council
(Amendment) Bill 1997", "District Boards (Amendment) Bill 1997",
"Societies (Amendment) Bill 1997", and "Public Order (Amendment)
Bill 1997".
</P>
<P>
Members will debate on a motion on "Increasing the Standard
Rate under the Comprehensive Social Security Assistance Scheme for
the Elderly".
</P>
<P>
After the plenary meeting, the fifth House Committee of the PLC
will hold a meeting to discuss "Means of public consultation made
by committees of the Provisional Legislative Council", "Seating
arrangements for members at council meetings", and "Ceremonial and
logistical arrangements for July 1 1997".
</P>
<P>
The Bills Committee on National Flag and National Emblem Bill
and Regional Flag and Regional Emblem Bill will hold a meeting to
discuss the two bills with representatives of the Chief
Executive's Office.  
</P>
