<HEADLINE> Chinese President's Interview With French TV Reporters </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 16 (Xinhua) -- President Jiang Zemin, in an
interview here today with Harrouard Philippe, deputy editor of the
"Antenne 2" of France, and other French reporters, answered their
questions about Sino-French relations and other issues.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that he has had successful talks with French
President Jacques Chirac, who is visiting China, and that they have
reached a common understanding about a wide-ranging of issues.
</P>
<P>
Jiang described the Sino-French Joint Declaration, which was
just signed, as a historic document, and said that it has laid a
solid foundation for the establishment of a comprehensive
partnership between the two countries and is a milestone in
bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
He said that since the world is moving toward
multi-polarization, China and France, as permanent members of the
UN Security Council, have important influence on international
affairs and should be aware of their heavy responsibilities.
</P>
<P>
Developing a long-term, stable, comprehensive partnership with
an eye on the 21st century, is not only in the interests of the
two countries, but is also conducive to world peace, stability,
and security, he said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
