<HEADLINE> Foreign Firms Invest in Packing Materials Business </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, May 16 (Xinhua) -- The Tiger Pack Shanghai Limited, a
joint investment of several firms from the US, Singapore, and
Germany, starts production here today.
</P>
<P>
The company, with an initial investment of 24 million US
dollars, uses German production equipment. It will produce 22 tons
of plastic film a day, in addition to some zinc paper.
</P>
<P>
Company executives believe that China has a huge market for
high quality soft packing materials but the market is also highly
competitive.
</P>
<P>
The company, located in the Songjiang Economic Development
Zone, plans to export 30-40 percent of its products.  
</P>
</TEXT>
