<DOCNO> XIE19970516.0156 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-05-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> BHP Leads Australian Share Market to Record High </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, May 16 (Xinhua) -- The Australian share market was
elevated to a record close today by a leap in the price of key
bluechip BHP and a strong resource sector, offsetting tumbling
bank stocks.
</P>
<P>
The all ordinaries index closed 13.1 points up to 2538.1, after
reaching an intra-day high of 2539.5.
</P>
<P>
The previous record close on the all ordinaries was set earlier
this week, when the market barometer reached 2634.3 on May 13.
</P>
<P>
The share of BHP, the Broken Hill Proprietary Company Limited,
jumped 55.9 cents, or 3.08 percent, to 18.689 Australian dollars
with 7.879 million shares traded worth 145.7 million Australian
dollars (112 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Reynolds &AMP; Co senior broker Peter Struck said most investors
shifted out of the banks into the more attractive resource sector.
</P>
<P>
The all resources index jumped 30.4 points, or 2.13 percent, to
1460.3 while the all industrials fell 4.6 points to 3944.7.
</P>
<P>
CRA rose 38.3 cents to 20.41 Australian dollars, WMC lifted 21
cents to 8.08 Australian dollars, and Wooside Petroleum was 18
cents stronger at 11.20 Australian dollars.
</P>
<P>
The bank sector plunged 67.6 points to 4450.1 in the wake of
bleak second half earnings predictions from the majors.
</P>
<P>
Struck said sentiments that the profits have peaked contributed
to the fall of the share prices.
</P>
<P>
National turnover totaled 364.76 million shares traded valued
at 1.05 billion Australian dollars (814.8 million U.S. dollars),
with rises outnumbering falls by 586 to 460.  
</P>
</TEXT>
