<HEADLINE> Australian Dollar Lower on Rates Uncertainty </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, May 16 (Xinhua) -- The Australian dollar ended
marginally weaker here today in quiet dealings with traders citing
investor uncertainty over the short-term direction for the
currency.
</P>
<P>
The Australian dollar closed at 77.61 U.S. cents, down from
77.66 previously.
</P>
<P>
Traders said the domestic currency remained range-bound between
77.30 and 78.00 U.S. cents in the absence of any clear signals
from the Reserve Bank of Australia or the federal government on
the future course for interest rates.
</P>
<P>
A slide in the value of the U.S. dollar against the Japanese
yen this week, which put downward pressure on the Australian
dollar/yen and Australian dollar/U.S. exchange rates, also had
skewed market views on the local unit.
</P>
<P>
Traders said the Australian dollar might ease back next week if
the U.S. Federal Reserve opts to hike interest rates following its
policy meeting Tuesday although they think it unlikely the unit
will fall below 76 U.S. cents.
</P>
<P>
On the cross rates, the Australian dollar ended at 90.59/69
Japanese yen, up from 90.24/23.
</P>
<P>
It also was at 1.3213/25 German marks, up from 1.3146/58
previously.  
</P>
</TEXT>
