<HEADLINE> British National Carrying Heroin Arrested in Karachi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, May 16 (Xinhua) -- A British national carrying 1,400
grams of white heroin was caught today by Customs staff at the
International Airport of Karachi, Pakistan's biggest city, sources
said.
</P>
<P>
Cornish Mark Richard, 36, holding a British passport, was
arrested before he could board an Amsterdam-bound flight which was
leaving Karachi this morning via Zurich, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
During search of Richard's baggage, the Customs staff recovered
the contraband concealed in the secret cavities of his handbag,
they said.
</P>
<P>
In another case, the Customs Drug Enforcement Cell staff at the
airport nabbed two Ghanaian nationals following detection of
heroin they have secreted into their body cavities, they said.
</P>
