<HEADLINE> Angola Peace Lays Foundation for Democracy in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, May 16 (Xinhua) -- Democracy will take root in the
southern part of the African continent following the
consolidation of peace in Angola, said Namibian President Sam
Nujoma here Thursday evening.
</P>
<P>
Angola had entered a 'new period of peace' and this had
brought hope to the endeavour of the people to develop economy in
this region, Nujoma said at the banquet hosted in his honour by
Angolan President Jose Eduard dos Santos Thursday evening.
</P>
<P>
In Angola today, political differences had been put aside,
enmity ceased to exist and the pending issues in the Lusaka
Peace Accord would be solved through friendly methods and no
longer be delayed, Nujoma said.
</P>
<P>
In his speech, Angolan President dos Santos urged Namibia to
work in close collaboration with Angola in recovering the war
ravaged infrastructures in the areas bordering the two countries
so as to facilitate the promotion of border trade and the return
of refugees.
</P>
<P>
The two countries can engage in multi-faceted cooperation in
the areas of agriculture, engery and water, fishing, education,
trade and tourism, public health, social settlements, public
works and urban construction, transportation, finance and
culture, dos Santos said.
</P>
<P>
Namibian President Sam Nujoma started his state visit to
Angola on May 15 with the purpose of strengthening the friendly
relations of cooperation between the two countries. 
</P>
