<HEADLINE> China Works Against "White Pollution" </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 16 (Xinhua) -- China is moving against "white
pollution" caused by the heaping up of the used plastic products.
</P>
<P>
Ye Ruqiu, deputy director of the State Environmental Protection
Bureau, made the remark at an opening ceremony to launch a
publicity campaign against the "white pollution".
</P>
<P>
With the widespread use of the plastic products such as packing
bags and dinner sets, urban areas in China annually produce some
four million tons of plastic garbage, which cannot be treated.
</P>
<P>
Experts have noted that the final solution to the "white
pollution" problem is to develop the plastic products that can be
treated.
</P>
<P>
At present, one possible solution is to encourage enterprises
and consumers to use environmental-friendly products.
</P>
<P>
China has listed 32 enterprises and 67 kinds of products as
environmental-friendly over the past two years.  
</P>
</TEXT>
