<DATE_TIME> 1997-05-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Technology Markets Prosper in Zhejiang </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, May 16 (Xinhua) -- In recent years, as more
manufacturers became market-oriented and aware of science and
technology, demand for technology has been growing in east China's
Zhejiang Province, where technology markets have flourished.
</P>
<P>
Technology markets first appeared in the province a decade or
so ago in the form of "crop hospitals", "scientific and
technological development centers", "development companies", and
"intermediary companies", but their business was quite small.
</P>
<P>
Zhejiang is one of the areas which have seen fast economic
growth in China since it started its reform and opening-up drive
in the late 1970s and the province reports a billion yuan in
technology business annually, local sources say.
</P>
<P>
This has made it possible for technology markets to become a
permanent fixture in many areas, said an official in charge of
technology market work of the provincial commission of science and
technology. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970516.0188 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-05-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Enhance Education of Kids About Protection of Resources </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 16 (Xinhua) -- China will enhance the education of
middle school and primary school students about the protection and
rational use of natural resources, according to a high-ranking
Chinese legislator.
</P>
<P>
Wang Bingqian, vice-chairman of the Standing Committee of the
National People's Congress (NPC), said recently that this year
relevant departments will jointly compile a textbook on China's
natural resource situation for kids.
</P>
<P>
"To raise the awareness of rational resource utilization and
protection throughout society, especially the younger generation,
the NPC will pay greater attention to this," Wang said.
</P>
<P>
Wang said that China's natural resource situation should be
viewed correctly, that is, "neither too optimistically nor too
pessimistically."
</P>
<P>
According to Wang, the legislation and enforcement in this
regard will also be enhanced this year. "At present nine laws and
86 sets of administrative regulations have been issued in terms of
natural resource protection, but to meet the demands of new
situation, more laws and amendments should be formulated," he said.
</P>
<P>
"I hope the press will join us to give more publicity to the
utilization and protection of natural resources," he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
