<HEADLINE> Chinese Vice-Premier Meets Philippines Guests </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 16 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-Premier Jiang Chunyun
met here today with a delegation from the Filipino-Chinese General
Chamber of Commerce (FCGCC) and the Chamber of International Trade
of the Philippines led by FCGCC Chairman James G.Dy.
</P>
<P>
Jiang spoke highly of the efforts made by the two chambers in
developing friendship and economic and trade ties between China
and the Philippines, hoping they will play an even more important
role in enhancing such relations.
</P>
<P>
The guests' visit aims to know about the latest development of
China's reform and opening up drive, economic development, trade
policy, and environment for investment and to seek more
opportunities for cooperation in this regard.
</P>
