<HEADLINE> Light Industry Export Sees Further Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 16 (Xinhua) -- China's light industry earned
10.331 billion US dollars through export during the first quarter
of this year, 24.61 percent more than the same period last year,
according to a report from the China Light Industry Council.
</P>
<P>
With the exception of clocks and watches, exports of all other
light industry products saw a double-digit growth rate.
</P>
<P>
China's export of bicycles enjoyed the biggest increase, at
215.7 percent. Export of ceramics, lighting equipment, plastics,
toys, and silk embroidery registered faster growth rates above the
national average. 
</P>
</TEXT>
