<HEADLINE> Jiangsu's Light Industry Draws More Overseas Funds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, May 16 (Xinhua) --Jiangsu Province of East China has
seen one billion U.S. dollars of overseas funds flowing into the
province's light industrial sector.
</P>
<P>
Local sources say that this amount makes up 40 percent of the
total fixed assets in the province's light industry.
</P>
<P>
By now, overseas investors have started some 1,000
overseas-backed joint ventures in the province's light industrial
sector.
</P>
<P>
With the help of advanced technologies and manufacturing
equipment brought in by overseas investors, the province has seen
improved quality in their local brand name commodities. 
</P>
</TEXT>
