<HEADLINE> Police Look Into Food Poisoning Incident in Manila </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, May 16 (Xinhua) -- Police said here today that they
have begun an investigation of a food poisoning incident that
victimized 27 people in the city.
</P>
<P>
The victims were rushed to two separate hospitals late Thursday
after eating cheese sandwiches they bought from a popular
foodchain store in Antipolo in the north of Metro Manila.
</P>
<P>
Samples of the food have been secured by the police for
laboratory test. Police said the victims now were all in stable
condition.  
</P>
</TEXT>
