<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Produces more Sugar This Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, May 16 (Xinhua) -- China turned out 6.66 million tons
of sugar in the 1996-97 refining period, registering a 6.9 percent
rise compared with the previous period, Xinhua learned here today.
</P>
<P>
The country plans to sow sugar-bearing crops on 1.6 million
hectares of land this year.
</P>
<P>
Provinces in southern China have completed sowing of sugar
crops. Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region, China's largest sugar
producer, planted sugarcane on 466,600 ha of land, which surpassed
the annual quota.
</P>
<P>
Yunnan Province has sown sugarcane on 210,600 ha of land,
24,000 ha more than the area for 1996.
</P>
<P>
An official predicted that China's sugar output is expected to
hit seven million tons in the 1997-98 period. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
