<HEADLINE> NZ Stocks Finish Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, May 16 (Xinhua) -- The New Zealand share market
finished the week on a positive note today, helped by a recovery
in Telecom shares.
</P>
<P>
The NZSE40 index ended 4 points higher at 2314 with a turnover
of 60 million NZ dollars (41 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Telecom shares rebounded 3 cents to 665 cents and accounted for
one third of the turnover. This was the first rise in the
company's shares since Telecom announced a lower full year profit
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Other leaders to gain included Carter Holt Harvey whose shares
rose 4 cents to 330 cents, Fletcher Building, up 4 cents to 404
cents, and Lion Nathan, up 1 cent to 356 cents.
</P>
<P>
Among the weaker leaders, Air New Zealand slipped 6 cents to
306 cents, and Brierley Investment went down 1 cent to 135 cents.
 
</P>
