<HEADLINE> New Commodity Exchange Firm Set Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, May 16 (Xinhua) -- A commodity exchange scheme, known
as Kapiri Commodity Exchange (KCE) has been opened in Kapiri
Mposhi in Zambia's Central Province by a private agricultural
asset management company, Cornplus, to help farmers market their
produce.
</P>
<P>
According to the local press today, the company's Executive
Director Mululula Chilufya said that the KCE will be used as a
vehicle through which farmers will buy and sell inputs and
agricultural produce.
</P>
<P>
The KCE is the second agricultural commodity exchange in the
country to one based in Lusaka. Some of its objectives are to
encourage the growth of the commodity market in Zambia by
providing trade information, good and fair mechanism for
commodity pricing.
</P>
<P>
It is expected to facilitate the marketing of agricultural
commodities by offering storage services and performing the dual
purpose of trading and distribution of produce.
</P>
<P>
It will also encourage the growth of commodity market and
provide a channel for speculative investment in the agricultural
sector. 
</P>
</TEXT>
