<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Local Election Campaigning Ends in West Nepal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, May 16 (Xinhua) -- Publicity activities for the
local elections to be held in West Nepal Saturday have come to an
end with the polls only one day away, election officials here said
today.
</P>
<P>
The Election Commission prohibited any political parties or
independent candidates from carrying out campaigns after Thursday
while all preparations for the elections have been completed, they
said.
</P>
<P>
According to the commission, Saturday's polls, as the first
phase of Nepal's local elections, will be held in 24
municipalities and over 1,800 villages of 40 districts in West
Nepal.
</P>
<P>
The local elections' second phase will be held on May 26 in the
country's other 35 districts in central and eastern districts.
</P>
<P>
Voters will elect a total of 190,000 officials at the village,
municipality and district levels across the country through the
elections to replace the incumbent local officials, who were
elected five years ago in the country's first local elections.
</P>
</TEXT>
