<HEADLINE> Ramos Flying Home at End of 10-Day Foreign Trip </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, May 16 (Xinhua) -- Philippine President Fidel Ramos is
flying home from a 10-day visit to the United States, Mexico and
Panama and is expected to arrive here this evening.
</P>
<P>
The president, who left on May 6, started his trip with a
working visit to Los Angeles before proceeding to Mexico and
Panama for state visits.
</P>
<P>
During the visit, Ramos met with Mexican President Ernesto
Zedillo Ponce de Leon and Panamanian President Ernesto Perez
Balladares for increased trade and investments between the two
sides.
</P>
<P>
Ramos also signed several agreements to boost bilateral
relations in trade, investments, cultural, scientific and
technical exchanges, along with cooperation in the fight against
drug trafficking and terrorism.
</P>
<P>
This is Ramos' 29th foreign trip of economic diplomacy since he
assumed office in 1992. Local press said Ramos' efforts had drawn
a total investment of 20 billion U.S. dollars into the country.
</P>
</TEXT>
