<HEADLINE> China Light Industry Sales Up 12.6 Percent in First Quarter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 16 (Xinhua) -- China's light industry sold 663.3
billion yuan worth of goods during the first quarter, up 12.6
percent over the same period last year in real terms, according to
the China Light Industry Council.
</P>
<P>
The growth rate is only 0.1 percentage point higher than that
for the corresponding period last year.
</P>
<P>
The sales volume in the urban area is 407.3 billion yuan,
increasing 13.8 percent on an annual basis. The sales volume in
the rural areas grew 10.6 percent annually.
</P>
<P>
The sales ratio for the light industry is 93.96, a rise of 0.9
percentage points over the same period last year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
