<HEADLINE> China to Cement Ties with Malaysia: Jiang </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 16 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin spoke
highly of the smooth development of Sino-Malaysian ties during his
meeting with visiting Malaysian Foreign Minister Datuk Abdullah
Bin Haji Badawi here today.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that the recent years have witnessed sound
advancement of the bilateral ties since the two countries share
each other's views on many issues.
</P>
<P>
For the long-term interests of the two countries, and peace and
prosperity of the Asian region as a whole, the two countries
should enhance their cooperation to establish mutual trust and
good-neighborly ties oriented towards the 21st century, Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
Badawi said that the leaders of the two countries have
exchanged visits frequently, and the cooperation of the two
nations in various fields have constantly increased.
</P>
<P>
Furthermore, Badawi said, China has made important
contributions to the development of the Association of Southeast
Asian Nations (ASEAN) by enhancing its ties with ASEAN and
actively participating in various dialogues and cooperation with
ASEAN.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that China stands for a multi-polar world because
such a world is beneficial to peace and stability.
</P>
<P>
As a big developing country, China would like to make its
contribution to safeguarding peace and promoting development, he
added.
</P>
<P>
Jiang also expressed appreciation at Malaysia's efforts to push
forward China's ties with ASEAN. He expressed his hope that
Sino-ASEAN relations would enjoy more progress.
</P>
<P>
Badawi spoke highly of China's rapid development in recent
years, saying that Malaysia and ASEAN have always regarded China
as a "good friend and good neighbor", and never hold the view that
a strong China will pose threat to peace in the region.
</P>
<P>
Those who hold the theory of "China threat" are ignorant about
China, he said, adding that Malaysia and ASEAN both believe that
China's development will make a positive contribution to the
peace, stability, and prosperity of the region.
</P>
<P>
Badawi conveyed Prime Minister Datuk Mahathir's warm regards to
Jiang, for which Jiang expressed his thanks. 
</P>
</TEXT>
