<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ruins of 2,500-Year Old Great Wall Discovered in North China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, May 16 (Xinhua) -- The ruins of part of the
2,500-year old Great Wall have been discovered in Tangxian County
in north China's Hebei Province.
</P>
<P>
The 10-km Great Wall ruins were found on the Maershan Mountain
near Caizhuang Village, 150 km north of the capital city
Shijiazhuang.
</P>
<P>
A local archaeologist said the Great Wall was built by
Zhongshan Kingdom (506-296 B.C.) in north China. The kingdom had
existed for more than 200 years under threats and attacks from
many powerful kingdoms in the Spring and Autumn Period (770-476
B.C.) and the Warring States Period (475-221 B.C.).
</P>
<P>
Archaeologists and historians still know little about the
kingdom owing to the lack of historical relics and records, he
said.
</P>
<P>
"The discovery will help strip away the myths of the kingdom
and prove that the country's oldest Great Wall was built in the
Warring States Period, 100 years earlier than the famous sections
of the Qin Dynasty (221-207 B.C.)," the archeologist added.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970516.0225 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-05-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Dhaka to Sign Peace Accord with Tribal Rebels </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, May 16 (Xinhua) -- The Bangladeshi government is
preparing to sign an accord with the tribal rebels in southern
Chittagong Hill Tracts (CHT) before the expiry of the current
ceasefire on June 30, according to sources.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the government also wants to sign the peace
agreement before the expiry of the tenure of the three hill
district councils on July 5, the sources added.
</P>
<P>
A consensus was reached on all issues on Wednesday between the
government delegation and the Parbatya Chattagram Jana Sahhati
Samiti (PCJSS), the political wing of the armed tribal rebels, to
bring peace in the trouble-torn CHT.
</P>
<P>
Ever since the 1970s, the independence-seeking tribal
insurgents have launched a bloody bush war, which cost thousands
of lives, in the 14,200 square kilometer region, rich in
hydrocarbon deposits and teak.
</P>
<P>
The government in the talks agreed to re-elect the three
district councils and will make those more effective under elected
leadership, having wide powers and enjoying special status with a
tribal person heading each and non-tribals also having adequate
representation.
</P>
<P>
The other main issues both sides agreed on are: the security
forces would stay in CHT in cantonments, Bangalee settlers are to
vacate occupied lands belonging to tribal people, insurgents are
to lay down their arms and the government will arrange their
resettlement under a package.
</P>
<P>
The PCJSS delegation, headed by Shantu Larma, has left Dhaka
Thursday afternoon for their makeshift headquarters, ending four
and a half days of negotiations with the National Committee on
CHT.
</P>
<P>
"We would be back in the city again to initial the peace deal,"
claimed Shantu Larma before his departure.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
