<HEADLINE> Foreign-Funded Wind Power Station Built in South China Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAINAN, May 16 (Xinhua) -- A wind power station in Dongfang
city in Hainan Province has completed its second phase of
construction to install 12 wind-driven generators with a capacity
of 600 KW each.
</P>
<P>
An 11.6 million deutsche mark low-interest loan from Germany
paid for the construction work that lifted the Basuo Wind Power
Station's installed capacity to 87 million KW.
</P>
<P>
One of the country's pilot projects to use overseas investment
to develop wind energy resources, Basuo station completed its
first phase of construction last year by installing equipment
donated by the German government.
</P>
<P>
The station is to use nearly 3.9 million US dollars of
interest-free loans from Denmark to carry out its third phase of
construction, to build another seven generators with a capacity of
600 KW each. 
</P>
