<HEADLINE> Malaysian King Leaves for Visit to Hungary, Poland </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, May 16 (Xinhua) -- Malaysian King Tuanku Ja'afar
today left for a state visit to Hungary and Poland.
</P>
<P>
Accompanied by his Queen Tuanku Najihah, the king left on a
Malaysia Airlines flight from the Kuala Lumpur International
Airport in Subang near here after a ceremony at Parliament Square
here.
</P>
<P>
The royal entourage includes Minister in the Prime Minister's
Department Abdul Hamid Othman and senior government officials.
</P>
<P>
The Malaysian king's five-day tour of East Europe was hailed as
a milestone in efforts to further improve bilateral ties between
Malaysia and the two countries.
</P>
<P>
This is the King's first visit to East Europe since assuming
the post in September 1994.
</P>
<P>
During the current visit, the king's programs include meetings
with the respective presidents, prime ministers and speakers of
parliament in the two countries.
</P>
<P>
In Budapest, the Hungarian capital city, the king is scheduled
to lay a wreath at the Heroes Square and be presented with the key
to Budapest by the city's mayor.
</P>
<P>
The royal visit to Poland includes a wreath-laying ceremony at
the "Tomb of the Unknown Soldier", a tour of the Old City and a
trip to Krakow, the old capital of Poland.  
</P>
