<HEADLINE> Soeharto: Business Partnership Must Be Fully </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, May 16 (Xinhua) -- Indonesian President Soeharto urged
big businessmen to fully implement the government business
partnership program which they have pledged to support.
</P>
<P>
Addressing businessmen attending the 1997 business partnership
meeting Thursday in Bogor Palace, West Java, the president said
that the program was a constitutional mandate, reports reaching
here today said.
</P>
<P>
At least 600 conglomerates and small businessmen attended the
meeting.
</P>
<P>
Partnership activities should be based on mutual benefit and
interdependence, said the president.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out, "partnership is not an ordinary cooperation,
but should be accompanied by education and development from big
business in order to assist small enterprise."
</P>
<P>
Soeharto launched a national business partnership forum in May
last year to boost cooperation between large and small
enterprises.
</P>
<P>
The forum groups 41 large business leaders who signed a deal in
Jimbaran, Bali, to help the government eradicate poverty by
forging a partnership with small enterprises and cooperatives.
</P>
<P>
The group has set up Pt. Mitra Dana Jimbaran with paid-up
capital of 50 billion rupiah (22.2 million US dollars) to provide
cheap financing to targeted enterprises and cooperatives.
</P>
<P>
Up to now, Soeharto said, several partnerships have been
established in seven provinces involving 600 conglomerates and
300,000 small business and cooperatives.
</P>
<P>
"Partnership between large and small enterprises will help
Indonesian business face economic globalization and will also
modernize Indonesia's economy," Soeharto added.
</P>
<P>
There are 34 million cooperatives comprising small-scale
enterprises in Indonesia, who are eager to participate in the
partnership program. Minister of Cooperatives and Small
Enterprises Subiakto Tjakrawerdaya said the number could be
covered by the program in 10 years.  
</P>
</TEXT>
