<HEADLINE>   More Than 6,400 in Albania Multinational Force </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, May 15 (Xinhua) -- The Italian-led Multinational
Protection Force (MPF) deployed in Albania now numbers 6,400,
Italian Defense Minister Beniamino Andreatta said in a report to
the parliament today.
</P>
<P>
He said the MPF in Albania would shortly be expanding its
deployment northwards, eastwards and southwards.
</P>
<P>
At present, MPF detachments were stationed at Lezhe and Shengin
in the north, at Durres, Tirana, Elbasan and Fier in the centre
and at Vlore and Gjirokaster in south.
</P>
<P>
The force's units carried out daily patrols to ensure freedom
of movement in the cities and along main roads by day and night,
Andreatta said.
</P>
<P>
He stressed the difference between Italy's commitment within
the MPF to help create a climate of security in Albania, and its
bilateral activities, which include naval and coastguard patrols
to try to reduce the number of Albanians fleeing across the
Adriatic to Italy.
</P>
<P>
More than 15,000 have so far fled to Italy since the crisis
broke out in March, the report said.
</P>
<P>
Andreatta gave a breakdown of the composition of the MPF in
Albania showing the Italian contingent at around 3,000 men, the
French at 1,000, Turks at 780, Greeks at more than 700, Romanians
at 400, Spanish at 350, Austrians at 100 and the Danes at 60.
</P>
</TEXT>
