<HEADLINE> Over 3,500 Kilos of Narcotic Drugs Seized in Myanmar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, May 16 (Xinhua) -- About 3,594 kilograms of narcotic
drugs, including 681 kilograms of heroin and 2,905 kilograms of
different kinds of opium, were seized by the Myanmar authorities
in April, the official daily The New Light of Myanmar reported
today.
</P>
<P>
The seizure also included 148.95 liters of phensedyl, 3,636
liters of acetic anhydride, 74,140 amphetamine tablets and 7,528
liters of other chemicals.
</P>
<P>
The Myanmar authorities took action against 427 people in 314
drug-related cases in the month, the report said.
</P>
<P>
A total of over 2,000 kilograms of drugs was confiscated last
month, according to an earlier official report.  
</P>
