<HEADLINE> Thai Interior Ministry Steps Up Anti-Crime Measures </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, May 16 (Xinhua) -- The Thai Interior Ministry will
step up measures to suppress child prostitution, narcotics and
other crime at tourist spots, especially Pattaya, Phuket and
Chiang Mai.
</P>
<P>
Police will take legal action against certain foreigners who
abuse their rights by virtue of marriage to Thai women to run
illegal businesses in Pattaya, the ministry's deputy spokesman
Atthasith Sapphayasith was quoted today by local press as saying.
</P>
<P>
Officials are to take serious action on drug abuse among
foreign tourists and on the holding of the so-called full moon
parties at some tourist spots, including Pha-nagan Island in Surat
Thani province, southern Thailand, he said.
</P>
<P>
Special police task forces, which are cleaning up Pattaya, will
be dispatched to Chiang Mai, Phuket, Hatyai and Pha-nagan Island
soon, Atthasith said.  
