<P>
MEXICO CITY, May 15 (Xinhua) -- Mexican President Ernesto
Zedillo announced today that this year's federal spending for
education will reach 118 billion pesos (about 15.128 billion
U.S. dollars), an increase of 7.2 percent in real terms over last
year.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a meeting marking the 79th anniversary of Teacher's
Day, Zedillo said the Mexican teachers have contributed to create
a country that desires to improve, because it has a future of
hope, prosperity, and justice.
</P>
