<HEADLINE> Sino-French Beer Joint Venture Set Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, May 16 (Xinhua) -- A Sino-French Beer joint venture was
set up this Thursday in Wuhan, capital of central China's Hubei
Province.
</P>
<P>
The Wuhan Euro-Dongxihu Brewery Co., Ltd. was funded by the
French Danone Group and the local Dongxihu Brewery
Corporation. Danone Group poured an equivalent of 320 million yuan,
holding 60 percent of the shares in the joint venture.
</P>
<P>
The joint venture plans to introduce a state-of-the-art bottling
line in the near future.
</P>
<P>
Danone Group, Europe's third largest and world's sixth largest
beer producer has an annual beer production capacity of 2.4 million
tons.
</P>
<P>
Wuhan Dongxihu Brewery Corporation, China's fifth largest beer
producer, has 370,000 tons in annual beer production capacity.
</P>
