<HEADLINE> Xi'an Development Zone on Expansion </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, May 16 (Xinhua) -- Work on the second phase of the Xi'an
New and High-tech Development Zone started early this month.
</P>
<P>
The expansion project, which will double the size of the
development zone, includes a science park featuring
program-controlled telephones and other communication facilities,
a multi-media and software park and an industrial park funded by
Taiwan investors. It will cover a total area of six sq. km when it
is completed by 2008.
</P>
<P>
The development zone was built in 1991 as one of the 52
state-level zones. The first phase covers 3.2 sq. km.. More than
2,200 high-tech enterprises have settled there.
</P>
<P>
By now, over 3,000 research findings from the zone have put
into production, yielding an industrial output value of 4.8
billion yuan.  
</P>
