<HEADLINE> China's Annual Sugar Production Hits 6.66 Million Tons </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, May 16 (Xinhua) -- China produced 6.66 million tons of
sugar during the last sugar production year, a rise of nearly
seven percent from the previous period.
</P>
<P>
China has 16 sugar production provinces, regions and
municipalities, including Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region, and
Guangdong, Yunnan, Hainan, Fujian, Sichuan, and Heilongjiang
Provinces.
</P>
<P>
Last year, the growing areas of sugar crops in the country
exceeded 1.33 million ha., nearly 427,000 ha. of which are in
southwest China's Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
According to an official from the region, Guangxi produced 2.34
million tons of sugar in the last production year in spite of the
severe drought and flood disasters. In addition, both Guangdong
and Yunnan produce more than one million tons of sugar a year.
</P>
</TEXT>
