<HEADLINE> Venezuela Increases Imports in First Quarter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CARACAS, May 15 (Xinhua) -- Import volume of Venezuela in the
first quarter of 1997 stood at 2.39 billion U.S. dollars, a 36.7
percent increase over the same period of 1996, a report issued by
the Statistics and Information Central Office said today.
</P>
<P>
The report said imports increased in all the productive
sectors. But by volume, the top three were electric materials
with 699 million dollars, chemicals with 292 million dollars and
common metals with 260 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
About 68.9 percent of the imports came from the United States,
Colombia, Germany, Brazil, Japan, Italy and France. 
