<HEADLINE> Ramos Rejects Early Anointment of Successor </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, May 16 (Xinhua) -- Philippine President Fidel Ramos has
rejected a recommendation to announce his choice of successor
before the ruling Lakas-NUCD party holds its national convention
late this year.
</P>
<P>
Lakas members at the House of Representatives, however, warned
that if Ramos ignores the recommendation, the party might suffer a
breakup, local press reported today.
</P>
<P>
The recommendation was made recently by a 16-member committee
set up by Ramos himself to set the criteria, procedure and
timetable for the selection of his successor.
</P>
<P>
"There is no need for them to recommend me to anoint early
because the Lakas convention is still out there, they should just
wait," said the president, who was winding up a 10-day visit to
the United States, Mexico and Panama.
</P>
<P>
Ramos did not say when he would reveal his choice. In the past,
he had said he had a long list of his would-be successors and the
list was becoming "shorter" each day.
</P>
<P>
It is reported that Ramos' anointment would ensure the success
of a candidate in the 1998 presidential elections since it would
translate into several millions of supporting votes.  
</P>
</TEXT>
