<HEADLINE> Romania, Moldova to Further Economic Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, May 15 (Xinhua) -- Romanian Prime Minister Victor
Ciorbea said here on Thursday that his country will further
develop economic cooperation with neighboring Moldova.
</P>
<P>
Ciorbea made the remarks at a press conference after meeting
with his Moldova's counterpart Ion Ciubuc, who arrived here today
for a two-day visit.
</P>
<P>
During the talks, the two sides agreed to promote the bilateral
trade which stood at 180 million U.S. dollars last year.
</P>
<P>
Romania will provide convenience for Moldova's exports to
Europe while Moldova will help Romanian commodities into the market
of the Commonwealth of Independent States.
</P>
<P>
They also discussed the establishment of two free economic
zones, one near the Romanian northeastern city of Iasi in their
border area and the other on the lower reach of the Danube, a
region connecting Romania, Moldova and Ukraine.
</P>
<P>
On the possibility of a merger of the two countries, which
have close ethnic ties, Ciubuc said "it is not suitable under the
current political situation."
</P>
<P>
Before the press conference, the two nations signed accords on
protection and immunization of crops, on cultural cooperation for
1997 and on cooperation between their justice ministries.
</P>
<P>
Ciubuc also held talks with Romanian President Emil
Constantinescu and the parliament speaker on Thursday. 
</P>
