<HEADLINE> Chilean President Meets Chinese Vice-Premier </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, May 15 (Xinhua) -- China wants to develop friendly
and cooperative relations, to expand trade exchange and to
increase reciprocal investment with Chile, said visiting Chinese
Vice-Premier Li Lanqing here today.
</P>
<P>
Meeting with Chilean President Eduardo Frei at the La Moneda
Palace, Li stressed the need to take advantage of the
complementary character of the two countries' economy.
</P>
<P>
Li told Frei that he had authorized the import of apple and
kiwi, and granted a partial authorization for the import of table
grapes from Chile, a grower free from the Mediterranean fly.
</P>
