<HEADLINE> Angola, Namibia Sign Aviation Accord </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, May 15 (Xinhua) -- Angola and Namibia signed here
today a bilateral aviation accord which enables each other to
open new flight routes.
</P>
<P>
Angolan President Eduardo Dos Santos and visiting Namibian
President Sam Nujoma monitored the signing ceremony.
</P>
<P>
Nujoma arrived earlier today to begin his official visit to
the northern neighbor. 
</P>
</TEXT>
